==Esperanto==
===Etymology===
Esperanto ''[[ki-]]'' (interrogative and relative [[:Category:Esperanto correlatives|correlative]] prefix) + ''[[-o]]'' (correlative suffix of objects)

===Correlative===
'''kio''' (''plural'' '''[[kioj]]''', ''accusative singular'' '''[[kion]]''', ''accusative plural'' '''[[kiojn]]''')

# [[what]] (the interrogative and relative correlative of objects)
#: Like other correlatives of objects, and unlike English ''what'', ''[[kio]]'' always functions as a noun, never an adjective. Like other interrogative and relative correlatives, '''kio''' can be combined with ''[[ajn]]'', the adverbial particle of generality. '''''Kio''' ajn'' thus means ''[[whatever]]''.

